# Cursor / Codex Agent Rules — The Janitor

## Universal Agent Protocol

All governance rules, commands, and skills are defined in `.agent_governance/`.
Read this directory on startup before taking any action.

## Mandatory Startup Sequence

1. Read `.agent_governance/README.md` — bootstrapping overview
2. Read all files in `.agent_governance/rules/` — hard operational laws
3. Read relevant files in `.agent_governance/commands/` before executing commands
4. Check `.agent_governance/skills/` for auto-invoked protocols

## Shared Ledgers (both agents maintain)

- `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_BACKLOG.md` — append every completed directive here
- `docs/INNOVATION_LOG.md` — P0/P1/P2 forward-looking proposals; never append completed work

## Critical Laws (summary — full text in `.agent_governance/rules/`)

- **Zero-Copy**: `memmap2::Mmap` for file reads; `rkyv` for IPC
- **Pre-Commit Gate**: Run `janitor_bounce` MCP before every commit; `slop_score == 0` required
- **Definition of Done**: `just audit` must exit 0 (fmt + clippy + check + test)
- **No Co-authorship trailers**: Sole author is Riley Ghramm
- **SAST Hygiene**: Static assertion messages only — no `{findings:?}` interpolation
- **Context Asceticism**: No exploratory reads; no sub-agents; fail-fast on ambiguity
- **Response Format**: Every directive response uses the 4-section mandatory format

## Version

Engine version is the single source of truth in `Cargo.toml [workspace.package].version`.
Never hardcode version strings elsewhere.
